  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2024-01-18",
    "date": "2024-02-14T15:17:49Z",
    "text": "Tax Excessive CEO Pay Act of 2024\n\nThis bill increases the current 21% income tax rate of corporations whose ratio of compensation of their principal executive officers or other highest compensated employees to median worker compensation is more than 50 to 1, in which case the increase is 0.5%. The pay ratio disparity extends from 100 to 1 to 500 to 1, in which case the increase is 5%. The bill exempts from such increase certain corporations based upon their average annual gross receipts."
  },
